    "description": "Grow your career with Kesari Tours South Asia Partners! We are hiring a Reservation Manager for our Tiruchirappalli team. Be part of a workplace that celebrates innovation, diversity, and performance.\n\nAbout Kesari Tours South Asia Partners:\nKesari Tours South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Deliver exceptional guest experiences in line with brand standards\n• Prepare daily operating reports and present to management\n• Manage front office operations including check-in/check-out\n• Coordinate housekeeping and maintenance for room readiness\n• Handle guest complaints and resolve issues promptly\n• Plan and execute banquets, events, and MICE functions\n• Monitor F&B service quality and maintain hygiene standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Event Management\n• Proficiency in Front Office\n• Proficiency in Barista Skills\n• Proficiency in Food Safety\n• Proficiency in Opera PMS\n• Proficiency in HACCP\n• Proficiency in MICE\n• Proficiency in OTA Management\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Kesari Tours South Asia Partners!",
